prompt.text: Name of the interviewer
Interviewer select your location.

[READ] Hello, my name is {{data.interviewer_name}}. I work with the Red Cross to support the community. I would like to ask a few questions to help the Red Cross better understand how it can help affected families. This will take approximately 15 minutes to complete. Your answers will be confidential, but we may share our analysis with other organizations who are looking to provide assistance. Do you agree to be interviewed?
Are you registering today due to Hurricane Dorian?
We will now register information about the members of your family prior the event
Household Members Section:
Please enter information about all the persons who normally live in this household
What is the best phone number to contact your family at?

hint.text: Country code, area code, number: must be 11 digits (1-xxx-xxx-xxxx) without dashes

constraint_message.text: Country code, area code, number: must be 11 digits (1-xxx-xxx-xxxx) no dashes

prompt.text: You must register at least one Household member!
Who is the head of the household?
Does head of household have any document or ID?

hint.text: Could be Government ID, NIB, Driving license, Voter's card, Passport, Membership card, etc. (Note when selecting 'Other' it can be a Haitian passport, membership card, or anything else that demonstrates an address or connection to community)

prompt.text: What type of ID does the head of household have?

hint.text: Ideally voter's registration card

prompt.text: Write the ID number of the NIB:

hint.text: 8 digits format

prompt.text: Write the ID number of the driving license:

hint.text: 9 digits format

prompt.text: Write the ID number of the voter's card:

hint.text: 6 digits format

prompt.text: Write the ID number of the passport:

hint.text: 2 capital letters and 6 or 7 digits. E.g. AA123456

constraint_message.text: 2 capital letters and 6 or 7 digits. E.g. AA123456

prompt.text: Write the ID number:
Do you have someone else we can contact, if we can't reach the household?
What is the first and last name of your alternate contact?

hint.text: Full name (first and last name). Make sure she/he doesn't use nicknames or an alias

prompt.text: What is the phone number to reach {{data.name_alt}}?

hint.text: Country code, area code, number: must be 11 digits (1-xxx-xxx-xxxx)

prompt.text: Do you confirm there are {{data.size_hh}} members in your household prior the event?

hint.text: (includes Head of Household and all members)

prompt.text: Please update the "Household Members Section" to ensure the correct number of people are registered as members of the household.
Have all your household members been accounted for since the hurricane?
Offer them access to RFL/PSS services via a visit to PSS Cottage in Nassau, hotline, or speaking to someone on your team (if available).
Are you hosting hurricane-affected people in your household?
How many people are they hosting?
Which island were you residing on prior to Hurricane Dorian?
In which community is your impacted home located? (city, village, neighborhood…)
Please specify which street/ neightborhood you are from in Nassau?
Please select the Neighborhood in Freetown
The interviewer has seen the proof of residence in Abaco or Grand Bahama of the registrant?
What language do you prefer for a potential follow-up?

hint.text: Do not suggest options, let the beneficiary express himself

prompt.text: Will you allow us to contact you with further information related to RC programs, via 3rd party messaging?
Did you rent or own your residence?

hint.text: Owner: for home owner insurance

prompt.text: Do you anticipate being able to return and live into your residence within the next 30 days
Is your household staying in one of the following?
Have you experienced the loss or disruption of income/ livelihood (fisherfolk, artisan, food vendor etc.) or operation of your small business?

Has your household experienced a change in family situation (for example, injury or loss of family member, or have additional people move in) and/or experienced emotional impact/ difficulty coping as a result of Hurricane Dorian?
Are you at risk of being without a stable place to stay – for example not being able to pay rent/mortgage, or not able to stay with your host any longer?
Special comments you would like to add:
Press next to calculate (or update) vulnerability score.

survey.name: total_vuln
survey.calculation: data('calc_gender_vuln') + data('calc_hh_size_vuln') + data('calc_island') + data('calc_owner_prior') + data('calc_returning') + data('calc_acc_type') + data('calc_vulnerability_hh') + data('calc_loss_income') + data('calc_risk_acc') + data('calc_family_situ')

prompt.text: Thank you for your time, have a nice day
